<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7406> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7406" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Quaestor and perhaps praetor of uncertain date in the late Republic. Despite the phrase quaestorius fuit nec ultra proficere voluit cum illi etiam Augustus consulatum offerret in Pomponius (Dig. 1.2.2.45), his refusal under the Triumvirs ut formulam componeret (Val. Max. 6.2.12), and the attribution to him of the iudicium Cascellianum (Gaius 4.166a, 169) suggest that he was urban praetor at some time under the triumvirate. (TJC)\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7406 .
